name: Maivious Summerlilly
text:
A hidden piece of paradise.  Beautiful park.  Quite!!
I love this place.
Make sure you bring something to drink.  No where to purchase food or drinks.  Please respect the park.

name: Sher Turner
text: It's a cool very large spider ina very green setting at the entrance to a boat yard and located close to the dinosaurs!!

name: Steve P
text: Another attraction with banmahinge and the dinosaurs in the woods. This one was roped off with a no trespassing sign when we visited, so we did not get to see it up close. Did get to see the other free attractions in the area.

name: A Blonde and A Brownie Bakery
text: Awesome place. Great for a spur of the moment get the kids out of the house type of thing. Don't forget to see the dinosaurs and Bamahenge while you're there.

name: Haley Doll
text: There was no sign saying what this was, we walked right by it thinking it was maybe just some abstract art with some weeds around it. It is big though! Found out later that it was a giant sun dial which is pretty cool! Wish I would have known that while I was looking at it though!

name: Sharon Brown
text: Bamahenge...there are no billboards, no signs on the highway. You drive along an impossibly green road, down the side road off a side road. You see something off to the right in the trees and realize it looks exactly like Stonehenge. Wait...in Alabama? There are places to park and a path that leads you to a full-size replica. After you visit, get back in the car and drive a way down the road looking for a place to turn around..a Triceratopsncomes into view. My theory is that Mr. Barber loves his grandchildren. Totally AWESOME!
